<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>HYMN FOR LAUDS FOR ADVENT AFTER DECEMBER 16th</B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am                 G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. The voices of the prophets
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                  Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   announce the Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   who brings to all men
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   the gift of peace.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. Behold a new light
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   lights up in the morning,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   a voice resounds:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   the King of glory comes.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. In His first advent,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Christ came to save us,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to heal our wounds
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in the body and in the spirit.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. At the end of time
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He will come back as a judge;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He will give the promised kingdom
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to His faithful servants.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. Now on our walking
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   His light shines:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Jesus, sun of grace,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   calls us to a new life.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C. You, Christ, we look for;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   you we want to know,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to praise you forever
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   in the blessed heavenly country.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. To you our praise, O Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   born from the Virgin Mary,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   to the Father and to the Holy Spirit,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                      G Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   for ever and ever. Amen.

</PRE></H3>
</BODY>
